Case Closed. Closed date : 2016-12-13 09:21:25.71 Case Resolved Arrived at address of complaint  34 Larchmont St. The backyard is not clearly visible from the street. The neighbor at 30 Larchmont St. did allow officer  to enter his yard to view the yard of 34. Officer Jones did see a dog enclosure in the back yard with a tarp over the top  a dog house  but no dogs were inside. The back door to the apartment  building was open  no dogs were seen in the yard at that time. Upon leaving the dog owner  identified himself. Owner was told about the complaint made. Owner did state he has 2 dogs  pitbull type dogs both females  both 1 1/2 years old. Owner stated he does not have any puppies. He also noted that the basement door is always open to allow dogs to come in and out of the house. The dogs were not seen at this time  nor where they were housed in the basement. Owner was given a license application along with a copy of the new tethering laws. Owner also was advised that when temperatures did drop that he keep dogs inside (Patti Jones  Officer #113)

Case Closed. Closed date : 2016-12-14 16:19:18.793 Case Resolved Contact was made with caller. Arriving at the location   callers home. Ms Santana stated that they got the cat from a friend  name not disclosed. No other information was provided  no vaccination history According to Ms Santana the cat was acting 'normal' until this morning. The cats behavior was described as follows  growling  attacking and biting at its tail  hissing. When I arrived I did observe blood trails all over floor. I also observed a DSH  tuxedo type cat   with blood on both paws. Attempting to approach cat growled  hissed . Ms Santana did state that the cat did not bite or scratch anyone as Bos 311 had reported  she just needed help putting cat in carrier. I placed the cat in a carrier and Ms Santana stated she was going to bring it to the MSPCA  to surrender..  This cat was not a stray  did not bite or scratch anyone therefore the caller  Ms Santana had to bring it to either surrender or get treatment.

Case Closed. Closed date : 2020-10-27 13:59:29.783 Case Resolved Animal Care and Control has received numerous complaints about this address. The dog owner has been spoken to on numerous occasions and at this point is willing to participate in a nuisance hearing (MGL c 140 sec 157). The dog owner states that the concerns are unfounded and the responding animal control officers have not found the dogs to be barking to create a nuisance- neither has the CSO for this district. We have spoken to at least one neighbor about this concern  as recently as last week  and that person did not identify the address as a source of nuisance barking.   A  resident called earlier today expressing concern that nothing has been done to address the situation. The 311 call taker conferenced me in and advised the resident that I was on the line. The resident was advised that he could remain anonymous by myself and by the 311 staff member  but he refused to speak with me. I tried to explain that we needed more information  but it appeared that the call was disconnected.   The dog owner has expressed that he feels that he is being harassed by the multiple interactions from the Division.  A Tracinzki
